VoiceTerm Repository Licensing Overview
======================================

This repository uses split licensing.

1. VoiceTerm application, packaging, and user-facing distribution surfaces are
   licensed under the MIT License in `LICENSE-VOICETERM`.

   The MIT carve-out applies to:
   - `README.md`
   - `QUICK_START.md`
   - `guides/**`
   - `img/**`
   - `rust/**`
   - `pypi/**`
   - `app/ios/**`
   - `app/macos/**`
   - `bin/voxterm`
   - `scripts/install.sh`
   - `scripts/setup.sh`
   - `scripts/start.sh`
   - `scripts/start.bat`
   - `scripts/macros.sh`
   - `scripts/macro-packs/**`
   - `scripts/python_fallback.py`

2. Unless a more specific local `LICENSE` file says otherwise, all other
   repository content is licensed under the restrictive proprietary terms in
   `LICENSE-AI-PLATFORM`.

   This includes the AI governance platform, `devctl`, repo-governance
   automation, control-plane/runtime tooling, Operator Console surfaces, and
   related integration/control code.

3. A subtree that ships its own local `LICENSE` file overrides this overview
   for that subtree. For example, `integrations/ci-cd-hub/**` continues to use
   its own local license file.

4. Third-party dependencies, vendored code, and generated artifacts remain
   subject to their own upstream licenses and notices.

If you need commercial, production, hosted-service, redistribution, or broader
usage rights for any content covered by `LICENSE-AI-PLATFORM`, you need prior
written permission from the Licensor.
